## Comments — `<%= @project.full_path %>`

Manage comments (notes) for this project via the Gisia API. Comments can be attached to issues, epics, and merge requests. Merge requests additionally support draft notes (pending review comments) that are published together as a review.

**Base URL:** <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>

**Authentication:**

```bash
curl <%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

The same five endpoints exist for each noteable type — substitute the parent segment:

| Noteable | Path prefix |
|----------|-------------|
| Issue | `/issues/:issue_iid/notes` |
| Epic | `/epics/:epic_iid/notes` |
| Merge request | `/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/notes` |

---

### List Comments

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

**Query parameters:**

- `order_by` (optional) — `created_at` (default) or `updated_at`
- `sort` (optional) — `asc` or `desc` (default: `desc`)
- `activity_filter` (optional) — `all_notes` (default) or `comments` to exclude system notes
- `page` (optional) — Page number (default: `1`)
- `per_page` (optional) — Items per page, max `100` (default: `20`)

---

### Get a Single Comment

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes/:note_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

- `:note_id` — Comment ID (the `id` field, not an iid)

---

### Create a Comment

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"body": "Your comment"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `body` (required) — Comment text (Markdown)
- `internal` (optional) — Boolean, marks the comment as internal
- `discussion_id` (optional) — ID of an existing comment to reply to. Replies to system notes are rejected

**Merge request diff comments:** on merge requests you may pass a `position` object to attach the comment to a line in the diff. When `position` is present a `DiffNote` is created.

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/notes" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "body": "This line needs a guard clause",
    "position": {
      "base_sha": "...",
      "start_sha": "...",
      "head_sha": "...",
      "position_type": "text",
      "old_path": "app/models/user.rb",
      "new_path": "app/models/user.rb",
      "new_line": 13
    }
  }'
```

**Position fields:** `base_sha`, `start_sha`, `head_sha` (required — the merge request diff refs), `position_type` (`text`), `old_path`/`new_path`, `old_line`/`new_line`, optional `line_range` for multi-line comments.

---

### Update a Comment

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes/:note_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"body": "Edited comment"}'
```

Only the comment author can update a comment.

---

### Delete a Comment

```bash
curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/issues/:issue_iid/notes/:note_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Returns `204 No Content` on success. Only the comment author can delete a comment.

---

### Resolve / Unresolve a Comment

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/notes/:note_id/resolve" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"

curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/notes/:note_id/unresolve" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

System notes cannot be resolved (returns `404`).

