## Draft Notes (Merge Request Reviews)

Draft notes are pending review comments on a merge request. They are private to their author until published. Publishing all drafts at once creates a review and notifies participants. All draft note endpoints require authentication.

**Path prefix:** `/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes`

### List Your Draft Notes

```bash
curl "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Only returns drafts authored by the authenticated user.

### Create a Draft Note

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"note": "A pending review comment"}'
```

**Fields:**

- `note` (required) — Comment text (Markdown)
- `position` (optional) — Same position object as diff comments above, attaches the draft to a diff line
- `discussion_id` (optional) — ID of an existing comment to reply to
- `resolve_discussion` (optional) — Boolean, resolves the parent discussion when the draft is published
- `commit_id` (optional) — SHA of a commit to associate the draft with

### Update / Delete a Draft Note

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes/:draft_note_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"note": "Edited draft"}'

curl -X DELETE "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes/:draft_note_id" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

### Publish a Single Draft Note

```bash
curl -X PUT "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes/:draft_note_id/publish" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN"
```

Publishes one draft as a regular comment without creating a review. Returns `204 No Content`.

### Submit a Review (Bulk Publish)

```bash
curl -X POST "<%= Gitlab.config.gitlab.url %>/api/v4/projects/<%= @project.id %>/merge_requests/:merge_request_iid/draft_notes/bulk_publish" \
  -H "PRIVATE-TOKEN: YOUR_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"note": "Optional review summary"}'
```

Publishes all your pending drafts as a review, optionally led by a summary comment (`note`), and notifies merge request participants. Returns `204 No Content`, or `422` when there are no pending drafts.
